en the\nAmerica\u2014also operated by the\nUnited States Lines\u2014went to sea\nonly to be made Into a Navy\nauxiliary vessel almost Imme\ndiately.\nBusiness Overestimating\nJobless, CIO Outlook Says\niv a* Shi\nThe CIOs Economic Outlook\nsays that business tried to under\nestimate unemployment during\nthe Repression apcS la tryip#, tp\norefEstimate now\n\"Somewhat strangely,\" th* pub\nlication said, \"large sections of\ntile business community that\nmade made such #4renuou*,a0or**\nto minimise the stae and impor\ntance of unemployment during\nthe 1930 s have now reversed\nthemselves.\n\"Journals of business opinion\nleading industrialist*, bankers and\nbusiness school professors are\nstressing the dangers and threat\nof unemployment Their motives\nof course, have not changed\n\"In the period of the '30s. they\nsought to minimize unemployment\nin an effort to forestall Govern\nment action to relieve it. Today,\nthey are stressing It* importance\nin order to convince Congress to\ngo slow In considering the admin\nistration's program of social and\neconomic reform which th# people\nvoted in 1948.\"\nBut while It complained about\nbusiness being worried over Job\nlessness now, the Outlook was\nworried, too It said business ha*\npurposely failed to expand enough\nand thereby failed to create\nenough jobs for the 1.000.000 per\nson* the publication says are\nadded to the labor force each year\n$500,000 Pledged Here\nFor United Jewish Appeal\nWashington buslnes* and pro\nfessional leaders pledged a total\nof more than 1500.000 toward the\nUnited Jewish Appeal at a pre\ncampaign dinner last night in the\nMayflower Hotel.\nThe contributions wtl! go toward\nthe Washington goal of *2,500.000\nin the campaign starting April 2*\nThe national campaign aeeks\n*250.000 000.\nPrincipal speaker at the dinner\nwas Samuel Rothberg, Peoria. Ill\nleader in the national appeal\nAsking for full support of the\ncampaign, he aald the money\nfrom this year s drive would be\nused for rehabi